The paper deals with models of interactive belief and the impossibility of agreeing to disagree, which are topics that fall under the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also uses logical reasoning and formal methods, which are relevant to the sub-fields of logic in computer science (cs.LO) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of certain assumptions and models, which is related to the sub-field of social and information networks (cs.SI).
